South African teachers in Vietnam are scared. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -South African teachers in Vietnam face the horrible prospect of being homeless. As COVID-19 grips the world, they are out of work and it's expensive to get home. READ: SANDF mum on army deployment It's no secret, South Africa has a very high youth unemployment rate. It's the reason many of these teachers opted to go work in Asia. READ: COVID-19 in SA: 402 confirmed cases Now they are in self-isolation and may lose everything they've worked for. Watch the video above for the full story #DStv403  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.